<subSubSection id="E0B775DB3C60FE3F18EBF949FE26F8F4" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="A81226503C60FE3F18EBF949FE26F8F4" blockId="9.[151,1436,1608,2008]" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">
Male imago: 1) turbinate eyes uniformly separated from each other, upper surface ellipsoidal; 2) terga with a light yellowish brown band along midline; 3) forceps with first segment distinctly constricted medioapically; 4) posterior margin of subgenital plate without a small rounded projection; 5) length of body relatively long (
<quantity id="6F558BB53C60FE3F197FF8D9FE2AF8F4" box="[337,433,1833,1859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
